        "author_association": "MEMBER",
        "body": "I agree, it doesn't seem we have much choice besides a warning for a future breaking change.\r\n\r\nThis would be a broader topic, but perhaps considering making Dask arguments such as `chunks=` [keyword-only](https://peps.python.org/pep-3102/) may be worth it, like we've done with the `like=` argument in NumPy. Such a change would help avoiding similar discrepancies between Dask and the other PyData APIs, plus I suspect few people would use `chunks=` as a positional argument today, but I may of course be wrong.",
