        "created_at": "2022-04-19T12:46:54Z",
        "updated_at": "2022-04-19T12:46:54Z",
        "author_association": "MEMBER",
        "body": "I think before undergoing this, I think a valid questions is whether or not numpy API compatibility is desirable.\r\n\r\nIt is conceivable that the original API writers thought that `chunks` was the most important second parameter.\r\n\r\nNow this doesn't work when people want to use `dask.array` as a drop in replacement for numpy, but I think it will rarely work.\r\n\r\nThat said, if the policy is to make `chunks` a keyword argument only, everywhere, I think that it is reasonable.\r\n\r\nI don't think you need to do an \"all in one rollout\", but I do think it is valuable to have a policy saying\"we will accept any PR that makes `chunks` a keyword only argument\".\r\n\r\nWhatever you choose, providing warnings to the users is useful. \r\n\r\nA while back I designed decorators that would enable the design of the deprecation policy and the warnings for you at the time of writing, you could leave them in at infinitum, or you could  remove them during a cursory cleanup.\r\n\r\nThey also ensure to pass on the warning to the correct stacklevel, something that seems to always be forgotten:\r\nhttps://github.com/hmaarrfk/wabisabi/blob/master/wabisabi/kwonly_change.py#L24\r\n\r\nscikit-image decided not to use them (but essentially rewrote the same idea) when they decided to have larger changes in their API.",
